#Title#
Parent Guide to Google Play - Google Play Help
#Content#
Google Play Help Google Play Help Google Play Help forumForum Contact us Information for families Parent Guide to Google Play Explore the topics below to learn about features for families in Google Play. Find family-friendly content Open the Play Store app on your device . Choose Apps & Games or Entertainment. If you selected Entertainment, choose Movies & TV or Books. Select Family. In the Books section, select Children's Books instead. From here, you can also browse content by age, family categories, or popular characters. Tip: You can also spot family-friendly content across Google Play by looking for the family star . The star tells you what age the content was designed for. Learn more Turn on password protection To help prevent accidental or unwanted purchases on your device, you can require authentication for Google Play purchases. Note: For apps and games that are labeled for ages 0-12 on the star badge, a password is required for in-app purchases, even if you don't usually require one. Learn more Ads in Family apps When apps and games show ads inside the app, you'll see an "Ad-supported family app" label. Ads are expected to be consistent with the maturity rating of the app or game. If you see ads that aren't appropriate for the age group the app was designed for, you can report the ad to Google. Use parental controls to restrict mature content If you share your device with others, you can turn on parental controls on your Android phone or tablet to block downloads or purchases of content by maturity level. You can choose different parental control settings for each type of content, and for each device. Learn more Set up a family on Google Play When you subscribe to the Google Play Music family plan, you'll create a family on Google Play, and invite up to 5 family members to join. With a family on Google Play, you can: See the purchases your family members make using the family payment method. Require purchase approval for in-app purchases, like virtual currencies or unlockable purchases. Note: Subscribing to the Google Play Music family plan and creating a family on Google Play is only available in certain countries. Learn more Share this: Dan is a Google Play expert and author of this help page. Leave him feedback below about the page. Was this article helpful? YesNo Submit Information for families Parent Guide to Google Play Set up & manage a family on Google Play Use a family payment method on Google Play Google Play Music family plan Join a family on Google Play Find family-friendly content Watch video tutorials To get the latest tips, tricks, and how-to's, subscribe to our YouTube Channel. ©2016 Google Privacy Policy Google Play Terms of Service Afrikaans‎ Bahasa Melayu‎ dansk‎ Deutsch‎ eesti‎ English (Australia)‎ English (Canada)‎ English (India)‎ English (United Kingdom)‎ español‎ español (Latinoamérica)‎ Filipino‎ français‎ français (Canada)‎ hrvatski‎ Indonesia‎ italiano‎ latviešu‎ lietuvių‎ magyar‎ Nederlands‎ norsk‎ polski‎ português‎ português (Brasil)‎ română‎ slovenčina‎ slovenščina‎ suomi‎ svenska‎ Tiếng Việt‎ Türkçe‎ čeština‎ Ελληνικά‎ български‎ русский‎ српски‎ українська‎ עברית‏ العربية‏ فارسی‏ ไทย‎ 中文（简体）‎ 中文（繁體）‎ 中文（香港）‎ 日本語‎ 한국어‎ English‎
